%% Validated against OpenHands-Cloud @ 136f63fdc

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Browser
    participant OpenHands as OpenHands (Enterprise Server)<br/>also hosts /bitbucket-dc-proxy/oauth2/userinfo<br/>(OIDC userinfo shim for BBDC)
    participant DB as SecretsStore
    participant Keycloak as Keycloak<br/>(Identity Provider)
    participant BBDC as Bitbucket Data Center<br/>(OAuth2 Provider)

    Note over Browser,BBDC: User Login Flow (Client-Side Initiated)

    Note over Browser: User visits /login (SPA route)<br/>Clicks "Sign in with Bitbucket Data Center"<br/>Frontend builds Keycloak URL<br/>window.location.href = url

    Browser->>Keycloak: GET /realms/allhands/protocol/openid-connect/auth<br/>?client_id=allhands<br/>&response_type=code<br/>&kc_idp_hint=bitbucket_data_center<br/>&redirect_uri=.../oauth/keycloak/callback<br/>&scope=openid+email+profile

    Note over Keycloak: kc_idp_hint=bitbucket_data_center<br/>skips login page<br/>(providerId=oauth2, generic OIDC broker)

    Keycloak->>Browser: 302 Redirect to Bitbucket Data Center

    Browser->>BBDC: GET https://<BBDC_HOST>/rest/oauth2/latest/authorize<br/>?client_id=<BBDC_CLIENT_ID><br/>&redirect_uri=.../broker/bitbucket_data_center/endpoint<br/>&response_type=code<br/>&scope=REPO_ADMIN<br/>&state=<keycloak-state>

    Note over BBDC: User authenticates to BBDC<br/>and authorizes the OAuth app

    BBDC->>Browser: 302 Redirect to Keycloak broker
    Browser->>Keycloak: GET /realms/allhands/broker/bitbucket_data_center/endpoint<br/>?code=<bbdc-auth-code><br/>&state=<keycloak-state>

    Note over Keycloak,BBDC: Server-to-Server Token Exchange<br/>(clientAuthMethod=client_secret_post)

    Keycloak->>BBDC: POST https://<BBDC_HOST>/rest/oauth2/latest/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code<br/>client_id, client_secret, code, redirect_uri
    BBDC-->>Keycloak: access_token (JWT: eyJhb...)<br/>refresh_token, token_type=bearer

    Note over Keycloak,OpenHands: Userinfo Fetch — hairpins through public ingress<br/>back to the OpenHands server<br/>(BBDC has no native OIDC userinfo endpoint)

    Keycloak->>OpenHands: GET https://<WEB_HOST>/bitbucket-dc-proxy/oauth2/userinfo<br/>Authorization: Bearer <bbdc-access-token>
    OpenHands->>BBDC: GET /rest/api/latest/users/~<username><br/>(or /plugins/.../whoami) using bearer token
    BBDC-->>OpenHands: BBDC user JSON (id, name, emailAddress, displayName)
    OpenHands-->>Keycloak: OIDC userinfo claims<br/>{sub, email, name, given_name, family_name, preferred_username}

    Note over Keycloak: Creates/updates user<br/>Stores BBDC token (storeToken: true)<br/>id-mapper: sub → user attribute bitbucket_data_center_id<br/>identity-provider: hardcoded "bitbucket_data_center"

    Keycloak->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OpenHands
    Browser->>OpenHands: GET /oauth/keycloak/callback<br/>?code=<keycloak-auth-code><br/>&session_state=<uuid><br/>&iss=.../realms/allhands

    Note over OpenHands,Keycloak: Server-to-Server Token Exchange

    OpenHands->>Keycloak: POST /realms/allhands/protocol/openid-connect/token<br/>client_id, client_secret, code, grant_type=authorization_code
    Keycloak-->>OpenHands: access_token, refresh_token, id_token

    OpenHands->>Keycloak: GET /realms/allhands/protocol/openid-connect/userinfo<br/>Authorization: Bearer <keycloak_access_token>
    Keycloak-->>OpenHands: User claims (sub, email,<br/>bitbucket_data_center_id, identity_provider)

    Note over OpenHands: Logs:<br/>"Logging in user <uuid> in org <uuid>"<br/>"Full IDP is bitbucket_data_center"<br/>"user_logged_in" idp=bitbucket_data_center idp_type=oidc

    Note over OpenHands,Keycloak: Fetch & Store BBDC Token from Keycloak Broker

    OpenHands->>Keycloak: GET /realms/allhands/broker/bitbucket_data_center/token<br/>Authorization: Bearer <keycloak_access_token>
    Keycloak-->>OpenHands: BBDC access_token (JWT: eyJhb...)

    OpenHands->>DB: Store BBDC token in SecretsStore

    Note over OpenHands: User logged in<br/>Session created

    Note over OpenHands: server/routes/auth.py branches on two<br/>independent flags - valid_offline_token and<br/>has_accepted_tos. First login fails both.<br/>Returning users typically pass both.

    alt has_accepted_tos == false (first login)
        OpenHands->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /accept-tos (SPA page)
        Note over Browser: User accepts TOS on SPA page
        Browser->>OpenHands: POST /api/accept_tos
        Note over OpenHands: Log: "User <uuid> accepted TOS"
        OpenHands-->>Browser: 200 OK, body has redirect_url<br/>(NOT a 302)
        Note over Browser: SPA reads redirect_url and assigns<br/>window.location.href = redirect_url
    end

    alt valid_offline_token == false (first login, or offline session expired)
        Note over Browser,Keycloak: Second OIDC flow. Captures offline (refresh) token.<br/>Keycloak SSO session is live, so no BBDC round-trip.
        Browser->>Keycloak: GET /realms/allhands/protocol/openid-connect/auth<br/>&kc_idp_hint=bitbucket_data_center<br/>&redirect_uri=.../oauth/keycloak/offline/callback<br/>&scope=openid+email+profile+offline_access
        Keycloak->>Browser: 302 Redirect with new authorization code
        Browser->>OpenHands: GET /oauth/keycloak/offline/callback<br/>?code=<new-keycloak-code>
        OpenHands->>Keycloak: POST /realms/allhands/protocol/openid-connect/token
        Keycloak-->>OpenHands: access_token + LONG-LIVED refresh_token (offline)
    end

    OpenHands->>Browser: Set session cookies<br/>Redirect to app<br/>(returning users land here directly with no TOS/offline detour)

    Note over Browser,BBDC: Subsequent API Calls (BBDC Token from SecretsStore)

    Browser->>OpenHands: API request<br/>(e.g., GET /api/v1/git/installations/search?provider=bitbucket_data_center)

    OpenHands->>DB: Load BBDC token from SecretsStore
    Note over OpenHands: Log: "Getting token for user <email><br/>and IDP ProviderType.BITBUCKET_DATA_CENTER"<br/>"Got ProviderType.BITBUCKET_DATA_CENTER token: eyJhb..."

    alt access_token near expiry (less than 15 min left) and refresh_token still valid
        Note over OpenHands,BBDC: token_manager._refresh_bitbucket_data_center_token<br/>(gated by AuthTokenStore._is_token_expired<br/>with ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY_BUFFER = 900s)
        OpenHands->>BBDC: POST /rest/oauth2/latest/token<br/>client_id, client_secret, refresh_token,<br/>grant_type=refresh_token
        BBDC-->>OpenHands: new access_token + new refresh_token
        OpenHands->>DB: re-encrypt and persist
    else access_token still valid
        Note over OpenHands: Use stored eyJhb... as-is
    end

    OpenHands->>BBDC: REST API call with BBDC token<br/>Authorization: Bearer eyJhb...<br/>(e.g., GET /rest/api/latest/projects/.../repos)
    BBDC-->>OpenHands: API response

    OpenHands->>Browser: Response with data
